<p>It also has white sticker on front left/back right of roof rack.</p>', 'Check out  <a href="https://www.plonkit.net/curacao" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">www.plonkit.net/curacao</a> for more clues.', '["https://learnablemeta.com/images/x11G4T8kI0KIVtBq4RJ8M70BheNeB0ARs0K7.avif"]', '{"country":"Curacao","metaName":"Unique car","note":"<p>This black Street View car with a roof rack is unique to Curaçao.</p>\n<p>It also has white sticker on front left/back right of roof rack.</p>","images":["https://learnablemeta.com/images/x11G4T8kI0KIVtBq4RJ8M70BheNeB0ARs0K7.avif"],"footer":"Check out  <a href=\"https://www.plonkit.net/curacao\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">www.plonkit.net/curacao</a> for more clues."}', '2025-08-06 12:15:08', '2025-08-06 12:15:08');
<p>The only other countries with similar car are:</p>
<ul>
<li>Guam(English speaking, require front plates, you can usually see part of roof rack).</li>
<li>Northern Mariana Islands(English speaking, require front plates, antenna there will be noticeably closer to the camera)</li>
</ul>', 'Check out  <a href="https://www.plonkit.net/puerto-rico" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">www.plonkit.net/puerto-rico</a> for more clues.', '["https://learnablemeta.com/images/n9nB5rHvIS0mlgvv5WUO9H3q2sYji5GdxlNm.avif"]', '{"country":"Puerto Rico","metaName":"Unique car","note":"<p>A fully blurred Google car with a visible antenna on the front right, featuring a white dot on top, is common in Puerto Rico. Cars there don''t require front plates, and the language spoken is Spanish.</p>\n<p>The only other countries with similar car are:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Guam(English speaking, require front plates, you can usually see part of roof rack).</li>\n<li>Northern Mariana Islands(English speaking, require front plates, antenna there will be noticeably closer to the camera)</li>\n</ul>","images":["https://learnablemeta.com/images/n9nB5rHvIS0mlgvv5WUO9H3q2sYji5GdxlNm.avif"],"footer":"Check out  <a href=\"https://www.plonkit.net/puerto-rico\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">www.plonkit.net/puerto-rico</a> for more clues."}', '2025-08-07 08:31:15', '2025-08-07 08:31:15');
<p>(Jordan might resemble this landscape for new players, and it also has a black back on the car, so be aware of that.)</p>
<p>(Only other countries in South America with car like that are: Peru and Uruguay)</p>', 'Check out  <a href="https://www.plonkit.net/argentina" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">www.plonkit.net/argentina</a> for more clues.', '["https://learnablemeta.com/images/ENxdsByd6CHZbYAWzTCPjcA2LjK4LKkjqTYw.avif"]', '{"country":"Argentina","metaName":"Landscape + black car","note":"<p>If you find yourself in a flat, desolate, treeless, sparsely populated area with a visible black back of the Google car, you''re likely in Argentina.</p>\n<p>(Jordan might resemble this landscape for new players, and it also has a black back on the car, so be aware of that.)</p>\n<p>(Only other countries in South America with car like that are: Peru and Uruguay)</p>","images":["https://learnablemeta.com/images/ENxdsByd6CHZbYAWzTCPjcA2LjK4LKkjqTYw.avif"],"footer":"Check out  <a href=\"https://www.plonkit.net/argentina\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">www.plonkit.net/argentina</a> for more clues."}', '2025-08-07 08:31:33', '2025-08-07 08:31:33');
<p>You might also find rounded concrete or wooden poles in Brazil, but they are less common and can be used for region-guessing within the country.</p>', 'Description and images taken from:  <a href="https://www.plonkit.net/brazil" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">www.plonkit.net/brazil</a>.', '["https://learnablemeta.com/images/1/M8oDbVfsJXBswrWKzxVtcntoDyHGxFzarHPN.avif","https://learnablemeta.com/images/1/9a673uVB5sn4t4X2NLKfMUgRBcJ6eZstu3qY.avif"]', '{"country":"Brazil","metaName":"Pole","note":"<p>The most common poles in Brazil resemble a ladder at the bottom. They are rectangular, with long segments at the base and small holes near the top. Chilean poles look similar but have 1–2 larger sections at the bottom instead of 3+ like Brazilian poles.</p>\n<p>You might also find rounded concrete or wooden poles in Brazil, but they are less common and can be used for region-guessing within the country.</p>","images":["https://learnablemeta.com/images/1/M8oDbVfsJXBswrWKzxVtcntoDyHGxFzarHPN.avif","https://learnablemeta.com/images/1/9a673uVB5sn4t4X2NLKfMUgRBcJ6eZstu3qY.avif"],"footer":"Description and images taken from:  <a href=\"https://www.plonkit.net/brazil\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">www.plonkit.net/brazil</a>."}', '2025-08-07 08:36:02', '2025-08-07 08:36:02');
<p>In the photo, green checkmarks show the "real" Colombian cross, and red X''s show the ones that aren''t right.</p>', 'Description and images taken from:  <a href="https://www.plonkit.net/colombia" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">www.plonkit.net/colombia</a>.', '["https://learnablemeta.com/images/1/8Mab5U54QolSpRErChtOxBGiDQquMTd0S7Jn.avif"]', '{"country":"Colombia","metaName":"Colombian cross","note":"<p>Signposts in Colombia are made of <strong>white</strong> thin metal and have a distinct cross on the back.</p>\n<p>In the photo, green checkmarks show the \"real\" Colombian cross, and red X''s show the ones that aren''t right.</p>","images":["https://learnablemeta.com/images/1/8Mab5U54QolSpRErChtOxBGiDQquMTd0S7Jn.avif"],"footer":"Description and images taken from:  <a href=\"https://www.plonkit.net/colombia\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">www.plonkit.net/colombia</a>."}', '2025-08-07 08:37:31', '2025-08-07 08:37:31');
<p>You can find those in other countries:</p>
<ul>
<li>Philippines(vegetation,climate will be different)</li>
<li>USA(looks different,English instead of Spanish etc)</li>
<li>Guatamela(has car meta)</li>
