</ul>', 'Check out  <a href="https://www.plonkit.net/mexico" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">www.plonkit.net/mexico</a> for more clues.', '["https://learnablemeta.com/images/nc1uMDGhe51kmL2yT94NjrdkPCy8scsBvp4t.avif"]', '{"country":"Mexico","metaName":"Rounded electric counter","note":"<p>Mexico uses those circular electricity counters.</p>\n<p>You can find those in other countries:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Philippines(vegetation,climate will be different)</li>\n<li>USA(looks different,English instead of Spanish etc)</li>\n<li>Guatamela(has car meta)</li>\n<li>Dominican Republic(has car meta)</li>\n</ul>","images":["https://learnablemeta.com/images/nc1uMDGhe51kmL2yT94NjrdkPCy8scsBvp4t.avif"],"footer":"Check out  <a href=\"https://www.plonkit.net/mexico\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">www.plonkit.net/mexico</a> for more clues."}', '2025-08-07 08:38:38', '2025-08-07 08:38:38');
Only the capital Santo Domingo and the Northern city of Santiago de los Caballeros are covered.</p>
<p>With this landscape - similar cars can be found in Guatemala and Curaçao, but they lack the thick black stripes.</p>', 'Check out  <a href="https://www.plonkit.net/dominican-republic" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">www.plonkit.net/dominican-republic</a> for more clues.', '["https://learnablemeta.com/images/VZEhXwRmUJmZ5QC763iaBdNc6H2ZbWVbx9v5.avif"]', '{"country":"Dominican Republic","metaName":"Unique car","note":"<p>A Street View car with a white front and a roof rack filled with thick black rubber stripes is unique to the Dominican Republic.\nOnly the capital Santo Domingo and the Northern city of Santiago de los Caballeros are covered.</p>\n<p>With this landscape - similar cars can be found in Guatemala and Curaçao, but they lack the thick black stripes.</p>","images":["https://learnablemeta.com/images/VZEhXwRmUJmZ5QC763iaBdNc6H2ZbWVbx9v5.avif"],"footer":"Check out  <a href=\"https://www.plonkit.net/dominican-republic\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">www.plonkit.net/dominican-republic</a> for more clues."}', '2025-08-15 05:48:20', '2025-08-15 05:48:20');
<p>NOTE: These trident poles are not found in neighbouring Argentina and Brazil.</p>', 'Description and images taken from:  <a href="https://www.plonkit.net/uruguay" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">www.plonkit.net/uruguay</a>.', '["https://learnablemeta.com/images/311/SzvKKXP3BRxwLrTfPWujeiWG2Zbl4qwK4PyR.avif"]', '{"country":"Uruguay","metaName":"Trident poles","note":"<p>Uruguay uses a handful of different utility poles. One very common and useful one are the so-called trident poles, which get their name from their distinctive pole tops with three insulators that point upwards.</p>\n<p>NOTE: These trident poles are not found in neighbouring Argentina and Brazil.</p>","images":["https://learnablemeta.com/images/311/SzvKKXP3BRxwLrTfPWujeiWG2Zbl4qwK4PyR.avif"],"footer":"Description and images taken from:  <a href=\"https://www.plonkit.net/uruguay\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">www.plonkit.net/uruguay</a>."}', '2025-08-16 08:17:58', '2025-08-16 08:17:58');
<p>Note: You can find similar in Uruguay but landscape will be mostly flat and green.</p>', 'Check out  <a href="https://www.plonkit.net/peru" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">www.plonkit.net/peru</a> for more clues.', '["https://learnablemeta.com/images/315/XYQG1SQuJQQcQNWMl1x6213hfHL3fXkictQq.avif"]', '{"country":"Peru","metaName":"Kilometer marker","note":"<p>Peruvian kilometer markers are concrete, painted black and white, and sometimes display the road number at the top.</p>\n<p>Note: You can find similar in Uruguay but landscape will be mostly flat and green.</p>","images":["https://learnablemeta.com/images/315/XYQG1SQuJQQcQNWMl1x6213hfHL3fXkictQq.avif"],"footer":"Check out  <a href=\"https://www.plonkit.net/peru\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">www.plonkit.net/peru</a> for more clues."}', '2025-08-16 08:42:14', '2025-08-16 08:42:14');
<p>NOTE: The soil in western Rajasthan will be a lot more sandy and you’ll typically be able to see short desert shrubs.</p>', 'Description and images taken from:  <a href="https://www.plonkit.net/india" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">www.plonkit.net/india</a>.', '["https://learnablemeta.com/images/664/eRrvpzR2xm6jleHCbfr6nYE6EAJ9cswO4O7z.avif"]', '{"country":"India","metaName":"Gujarat Salt Flats","note":"<p>Salt flats and coastal marshes with nearly no vegetation, other than short yellow or brown grass, can be found in parts of Gujarat. Shallow bodies of water can often be seen around these areas.</p>\n<p>NOTE: The soil in western Rajasthan will be a lot more sandy and you’ll typically be able to see short desert shrubs.</p>","images":["https://learnablemeta.com/images/664/eRrvpzR2xm6jleHCbfr6nYE6EAJ9cswO4O7z.avif"],"footer":"Description and images taken from:  <a href=\"https://www.plonkit.net/india\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">www.plonkit.net/india</a>."}', '2025-09-10 07:41:10', '2025-09-10 07:41:10');
Closer to Villa Catalina, the car drove over the salt flat. Closer to Coipasa, the car drove on an unpaved dirt road, where you can see cone-shaped volcanic hills. In both parts, there is virtually no vegetation.</p>', 'Description and images taken from:  <a href="https://www.plonkit.net/bolivia" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">www.plonkit.net/bolivia</a>.', '["https://learnablemeta.com/images/664/hj7FQ15i2PBOpZOB6ZbHTgjiR2qZ6qWW3NQY.avif"]', '{"country":"Bolivia","metaName":"Chile Border Desert","note":"<p>Between the villages of Villa Catalina and Coipasa, there is an isolated stretch of coverage where the Google car drove through extremely arid desert terrain. This small road is located close to the southwestern end of Ruta 12, near the Chilean border. It can be hard to spot on the map, because it blends in with the salt flat.\nCloser to Villa Catalina, the car drove over the salt flat. Closer to Coipasa, the car drove on an unpaved dirt road, where you can see cone-shaped volcanic hills. In both parts, there is virtually no vegetation.</p>","images":["https://learnablemeta.com/images/664/hj7FQ15i2PBOpZOB6ZbHTgjiR2qZ6qWW3NQY.avif"],"footer":"Description and images taken from:  <a href=\"https://www.plonkit.net/bolivia\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">www.plonkit.net/bolivia</a>."}', '2025-09-11 08:33:06', '2025-09-11 08:33:06');
In the western provinces of Ciudad Real and Toledo, it is very common to see olive tree plantations, generally in flatter ground than those found in Andalusia.</p>', 'Description and images taken from:  <a href="https://www.plonkit.net/spain" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">www.plonkit.net/spain</a>.', '["https://learnablemeta.com/images/664/xUwGcjE5mO9S7ZiJoJVImuKpjMA8IN3j5XMb.avif"]', '{"country":"Spain","metaName":"Castilla La Mancha","note":"<p>Castilla la Mancha can have completely flat landscapes. Half of Spain’s wine is produced in this region, so vineyards are fairly common.\nIn the western provinces of Ciudad Real and Toledo, it is very common to see olive tree plantations, generally in flatter ground than those found in Andalusia.</p>","images":["https://learnablemeta.com/images/664/xUwGcjE5mO9S7ZiJoJVImuKpjMA8IN3j5XMb.avif"],"footer":"Description and images taken from:  <a href=\"https://www.plonkit.net/spain\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">www.plonkit.net/spain</a>."}', '2025-09-11 08:33:53', '2025-09-11 08:33:53');
<p>NOTE: The light red area has tall, sharp mountains to the northwest, and much lower hills and mountains to the southeast.</p>', 'Description and images taken from:  <a href="https://www.plonkit.net/slovakia" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">www.plonkit.net/slovakia</a>.', '["https://learnablemeta.com/images/664/InAk5zowdGkRH5MYBAPdujcR3VaawCdcRB4g.avif"]', '{"country":"Slovakia","metaName":"Mountains","note":"<p>Two wide valleys surrounded by tall, often sharp mountains can be found in the northern parts of the country.</p>\n<p>NOTE: The light red area has tall, sharp mountains to the northwest, and much lower hills and mountains to the southeast.</p>","images":["https://learnablemeta.com/images/664/InAk5zowdGkRH5MYBAPdujcR3VaawCdcRB4g.avif"],"footer":"Description and images taken from:  <a href=\"https://www.plonkit.net/slovakia\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">www.plonkit.net/slovakia</a>."}', '2025-09-11 08:39:42', '2025-09-11 08:39:42');
<p>The only paved road with coverage outside Kampala can be found here. The pavement almost entirely lacks the red tinge which is typical for most roads in the country. The road has white, solid outer lines and a yellow middle line.</p>', 'Description and images taken from:  <a href="https://www.plonkit.net/uganda" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">www.plonkit.net/uganda</a>.', '["https://learnablemeta.com/images/664/9wxcc01ugLoZPfqRlITTtHZ8v56KwlmoxMuE.avif"]', '{"country":"Uganda","metaName":"Crater","note":"<p>On the northern coverage, it is common to see large, water-filled craters. Similar craters cannot be found elsewhere in the country.</p>\n<p>The only paved road with coverage outside Kampala can be found here. The pavement almost entirely lacks the red tinge which is typical for most roads in the country. The road has white, solid outer lines and a yellow middle line.</p>","images":["https://learnablemeta.com/images/664/9wxcc01ugLoZPfqRlITTtHZ8v56KwlmoxMuE.avif"],"footer":"Description and images taken from:  <a href=\"https://www.plonkit.net/uganda\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">www.plonkit.net/uganda</a>."}', '2025-09-12 09:38:10', '2025-09-12 09:38:10');
<p>NOTE: Sandy soil can be found in many places in Botswana. This tip specifically refers to the bright white colour of the sand.</p>', 'Description and images taken from:  <a href="https://www.plonkit.net/botswana" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">www.plonkit.net/botswana</a>.', '["https://learnablemeta.com/images/664/kzuOmF7MwBJHMWjDOM9JkhO88VgegQRI0R45.avif"]', '{"country":"Botswana","metaName":"White Soil","note":"<p>A large region in the middle western part of the country is characterised by very white sandy soil. In addition, the vegetation tends to look very dry.</p>\n<p>NOTE: Sandy soil can be found in many places in Botswana. This tip specifically refers to the bright white colour of the sand.</p>","images":["https://learnablemeta.com/images/664/kzuOmF7MwBJHMWjDOM9JkhO88VgegQRI0R45.avif"],"footer":"Description and images taken from:  <a href=\"https://www.plonkit.net/botswana\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">www.plonkit.net/botswana</a>."}', '2025-09-12 09:45:41', '2025-09-12 09:45:41');
<p>NOTE: Flat areas of northern and eastern Oregon can have a similar appearance.</p>', 'Description and images taken from:  <a href="https://www.plonkit.net/united-states" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">www.plonkit.net/united-states</a>.', '["https://learnablemeta.com/images/664/G9ZND2WSXlbbO4y4oAuHH3PA9Mb9wh8t9uKT.avif"]', '{"country":"United States","metaName":"Washington Golden Fields","note":"<p>Agricultural golden fields can commonly be seen in eastern Washington.</p>\n<p>NOTE: Flat areas of northern and eastern Oregon can have a similar appearance.</p>","images":["https://learnablemeta.com/images/664/G9ZND2WSXlbbO4y4oAuHH3PA9Mb9wh8t9uKT.avif"],"footer":"Description and images taken from:  <a href=\"https://www.plonkit.net/united-states\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">www.plonkit.net/united-states</a>."}', '2025-09-13 12:05:27', '2025-09-13 12:05:27');
<p>NOTE: This area can look similar to the Great Lakes region in the US.</p>', 'Description and images taken from:  <a href="https://www.plonkit.net/canada" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">www.plonkit.net/canada</a>.', '["https://learnablemeta.com/images/664/menR0s7bDd3DGSWLF4dj6kUC5lvClOU4uN7Y.avif"]', '{"country":"Canada","metaName":"Québec City Windsor Corridor","note":"<p>The Québec City-Windsor Corridor is the most densely populated part of Canada. It is mostly flat and green, with a patchwork of agriculture and occasional forest cover.</p>\n<p>NOTE: This area can look similar to the Great Lakes region in the US.</p>","images":["https://learnablemeta.com/images/664/menR0s7bDd3DGSWLF4dj6kUC5lvClOU4uN7Y.avif"],"footer":"Description and images taken from:  <a href=\"https://www.plonkit.net/canada\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">www.plonkit.net/canada</a>."}', '2025-09-13 12:15:19', '2025-09-13 12:15:19');
<p>NOTE: Similar looking landscapes exist in some other parts of the country, but usually more level.</p>', 'Description and images taken from:  <a href="https://www.plonkit.net/chile" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">www.plonkit.net/chile</a>.', '["https://learnablemeta.com/images/664/skWQ5zYU8yNGWZaXgC8cDolevzE2PcRCIHRm.avif"]', '{"country":"Chile","metaName":"Isla Grande de Chiloe","note":"<p>A rolling, agricultural landscape, comparable to New Zealand, can be seen on Isla Grande de Chiloé.</p>\n<p>NOTE: Similar looking landscapes exist in some other parts of the country, but usually more level.</p>","images":["https://learnablemeta.com/images/664/skWQ5zYU8yNGWZaXgC8cDolevzE2PcRCIHRm.avif"],"footer":"Description and images taken from:  <a href=\"https://www.plonkit.net/chile\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">www.plonkit.net/chile</a>."}', '2025-09-13 12:16:09', '2025-09-13 12:16:09');
<p>NOTE: Pan de Azúcar National Park looks similar, however has less vegetation.</p>', 'Description and images taken from:  <a href="https://www.plonkit.net/chile" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">www.plonkit.net/chile</a>.', '["https://learnablemeta.com/images/664/h2l853aS0RiaPvZcmbZemM3vg5oR49tQsxn2.avif"]', '{"country":"Chile","metaName":"Llanos des Challe National Park","note":"<p>Llanos de Challe National Park can be recognized by the brown coloured dirt on the roadside, patches of light sand, juniper plants, and dark coloured mountains. The sky is overcast in most of the coverage.</p>\n<p>NOTE: Pan de Azúcar National Park looks similar, however has less vegetation.</p>","images":["https://learnablemeta.com/images/664/h2l853aS0RiaPvZcmbZemM3vg5oR49tQsxn2.avif"],"footer":"Description and images taken from:  <a href=\"https://www.plonkit.net/chile\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">www.plonkit.net/chile</a>."}', '2025-09-13 12:17:35', '2025-09-13 12:17:35');
